---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Food Assistance Eligibility"
  description="Learn about eligibility for CalFresh (food stamps), WIC, food banks, and other food assistance programs in the Bay Area."
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container-page">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <!-- Breadcrumb -->
        <nav class="mb-6 text-sm" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
          <ol class="flex items-center gap-2">
            <li>
              <a href="/eligibility" class="text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-300 hover:underline"
                >Eligibility Guides</a
              >
            </li>
            <li class="text-neutral-400">/</li>
            <li class="text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">Food Assistance</li>
          </ol>
        </nav>

        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-4">
          Food Assistance Programs
        </h1>
        <p class="text-lg text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-8">
          California offers several programs to help with food costs, from monthly grocery benefits
          to free food distributions. You may qualify for more than one program.
        </p>

        <!-- Legal Disclaimer -->
        <div
          class="bg-amber-50 dark:bg-amber-900/20 border-l-4 border-amber-500 p-4 rounded-r-lg mb-8"
        >
          <p class="text-sm text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300">
            <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide provides general information only and is not legal
            or professional advice. Eligibility requirements may vary by individual circumstances, and
            additional requirements may apply. To determine your actual eligibility, please apply directly
            to the program. Information is subject to change without notice.
          </p>
        </div>

        <hr class="my-8 border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-700" />

        <!-- CalFresh Section -->
        <div class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-4">
            CalFresh
            <span class="text-lg font-normal text-neutral-500 dark:text-neutral-400"
              >— Monthly Grocery Money (Food Stamps/SNAP/EBT)</span
            >
          </h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-4">
            CalFresh is California's version of SNAP (the Supplemental Nutrition Assistance
            Program), often called "food stamps." You receive monthly benefits on an EBT card that
            works like a debit card at grocery stores, farmers markets, and many other food
            retailers.
          </p>

          <div class="bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-3">
              Income Limits (Gross Monthly Income)
            </h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
              <li>• <strong>1 person:</strong> Up to $1,580/month</li>
              <li>• <strong>2 people:</strong> Up to $2,137/month</li>
              <li>• <strong>3 people:</strong> Up to $2,694/month</li>
              <li>• <strong>4 people:</strong> Up to $3,250/month</li>
              <li>• <strong>Each additional person:</strong> Add ~$557</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500 dark:text-neutral-400 mt-3">
              These are gross income limits (before taxes). Seniors and people with disabilities may
              have higher limits based on net income.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-3">
              How Much You Could Get (Maximum Monthly Benefits)
            </h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
              <li>• <strong>1 person:</strong> Up to $292/month</li>
              <li>• <strong>2 people:</strong> Up to $536/month</li>
              <li>• <strong>3 people:</strong> Up to $768/month</li>
              <li>• <strong>4 people:</strong> Up to $973/month</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500 dark:text-neutral-400 mt-3">
              Actual amount depends on your income, expenses, and household size.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-3">Basic Requirements</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
              <li>• California resident</li>
              <li>• Meet income and resource limits</li>
              <li>• U.S. citizen or qualified immigrant</li>
              <li>• Social Security number (or applied for one)</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div
            class="bg-primary-50 dark:bg-primary-900/20 border-l-4 border-primary-500 p-4 rounded-r-lg mb-6"
          >
            <p class="text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300">
              <strong>College students:</strong> You may qualify if you work 20+ hours/week, participate
              in work-study, have children, or receive CalWORKs.
            </p>
          </div>

          <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-3">How to Apply</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-4">
            <li>
              • <strong>Online (fastest):</strong>
              <a
                href="https://www.getcalfresh.org"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-300 hover:underline">GetCalFresh.org</a
              > — Simple application in about 10 minutes
            </li>
            <li>
              • <strong>BenefitsCal:</strong>
              <a
                href="https://benefitscal.com"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-300 hover:underline">BenefitsCal.com</a
              > — Apply for multiple programs at once
            </li>
            <li>• <strong>Phone:</strong> Contact your county office</li>
            <li>• <strong>In person:</strong> County social services office</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <hr class="my-8 border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-700" />

        <!-- WIC Section -->
        <div class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-4">
            WIC
            <span class="text-lg font-normal text-neutral-500 dark:text-neutral-400"
              >— Free Food for Pregnant Women, Babies & Young Kids</span
            >
          </h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-4">
            WIC (Women, Infants, and Children) provides free healthy food, nutrition education, and
            breastfeeding support for pregnant and postpartum women, infants, and children up to age
            5.
          </p>

          <div class="bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-3">Who Qualifies</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
              <li>• <strong>Pregnant women</strong> at any stage of pregnancy</li>
              <li>
                • <strong>New mothers</strong> up to 6 months after delivery (or 12 months if breastfeeding)
              </li>
              <li>• <strong>Infants</strong> from birth to 12 months</li>
              <li>• <strong>Children</strong> from 1 to 5 years old</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-3">Income Limits</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
              <li>• <strong>1 person:</strong> Up to $2,096/month</li>
              <li>• <strong>2 people:</strong> Up to $2,823/month</li>
              <li>• <strong>3 people:</strong> Up to $3,551/month</li>
              <li>• <strong>4 people:</strong> Up to $4,279/month</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500 dark:text-neutral-400 mt-3">
              Higher limits than CalFresh! If you receive Medi-Cal, CalFresh, or CalWORKs, you
              automatically qualify income-wise.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-3">What You Get</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
              <li>
                • Monthly food benefits for milk, cheese, eggs, cereal, fruits, vegetables, whole
                grains
              </li>
              <li>• Baby formula, baby food, and infant cereal</li>
              <li>• Benefits loaded onto a WIC card</li>
              <li>• Nutrition education and breastfeeding support</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div
            class="bg-primary-50 dark:bg-primary-900/20 border-l-4 border-primary-500 p-4 rounded-r-lg mb-6"
          >
            <p class="text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300">
              <strong>Immigration status doesn't matter for WIC.</strong> WIC is available regardless
              of immigration status and does not affect immigration applications.
            </p>
          </div>

          <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-3">How to Apply</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-4">
            <li>
              • <strong>Online:</strong>
              <a
                href="https://www.myfamily.wic.ca.gov"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-300 hover:underline"
                >MyFamily.WIC.ca.gov</a
              >
            </li>
            <li>
              • <strong>Phone:</strong>
              <a
                href="tel:1-888-942-9675"
                class="text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-300 hover:underline"
                >1-888-WIC-WORKS (1-888-942-9675)</a
              >
            </li>
            <li>• <strong>In person:</strong> Local WIC office (often at clinics and hospitals)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <hr class="my-8 border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-700" />

        <!-- Food Banks Section -->
        <div class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-4">
            Food Banks & Pantries
            <span class="text-lg font-normal text-neutral-500 dark:text-neutral-400"
              >— Free Groceries, No Application Needed</span
            >
          </h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-4">
            Food banks and pantries provide free groceries to anyone who needs them. Most locations
            have no income verification, no paperwork, and no questions asked.
          </p>

          <div class="bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-3">Who Can Get Food</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
              <li>• <strong>Anyone who needs food</strong> — no income limits at most locations</li>
              <li>• No ID or proof of income usually required</li>
              <li>• No citizenship or immigration requirements</li>
              <li>• You can use food banks even if you receive CalFresh</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-3">Bay Area Food Banks</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-3 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
              <li>
                <strong>SF-Marin Food Bank:</strong> Serves San Francisco & Marin<br />
                <a
                  href="https://www.sfmfoodbank.org"
                  target="_blank"
                  rel="noopener noreferrer"
                  class="text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-300 hover:underline">sfmfoodbank.org</a
                > |
                <a
                  href="tel:415-282-1900"
                  class="text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-300 hover:underline">415-282-1900</a
                >
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Alameda County Community Food Bank:</strong> Serves Alameda County<br />
                <a
                  href="https://www.accfb.org"
                  target="_blank"
                  rel="noopener noreferrer"
                  class="text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-300 hover:underline">accfb.org</a
                > |
                <a
                  href="tel:510-635-3663"
                  class="text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-300 hover:underline">510-635-3663</a
                >
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Second Harvest of Silicon Valley:</strong> Serves Santa Clara & San Mateo<br
                />
                <a
                  href="https://www.shfb.org"
                  target="_blank"
                  rel="noopener noreferrer"
                  class="text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-300 hover:underline">shfb.org</a
                > |
                <a
                  href="tel:1-800-984-3663"
                  class="text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-300 hover:underline">1-800-984-3663</a
                >
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Food Bank of Contra Costa & Solano:</strong> Serves Contra Costa & Solano<br
                />
                <a
                  href="https://www.foodbankccs.org"
                  target="_blank"
                  rel="noopener noreferrer"
                  class="text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-300 hover:underline">foodbankccs.org</a
                > |
                <a
                  href="tel:925-676-7543"
                  class="text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-300 hover:underline">925-676-7543</a
                >
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-3">
            How to Find Food Near You
          </h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-4">
            <li>• <strong>Call 211</strong> for local food resources</li>
            <li>• Visit your local food bank's website for distribution schedules</li>
            <li>• Many churches, schools, and community centers have food pantries</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <hr class="my-8 border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-700" />

        <!-- Free Meals Section -->
        <div class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-4">
            Free Meals
            <span class="text-lg font-normal text-neutral-500 dark:text-neutral-400"
              >— Community Meals, School Meals & Senior Meals</span
            >
          </h2>

          <div class="bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-3">School Meals</h3>
            <p class="text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-2">
              California provides free breakfast and lunch to all students at public schools — no
              application needed.
            </p>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
              <li>• All K-12 public school students qualify</li>
              <li>• No income verification required</li>
              <li>• Summer meal programs available at many locations</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-3">Senior Meals (60+)</h3>
            <p class="text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-2">
              Free meals for adults 60 and older through congregate dining and home delivery.
            </p>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
              <li>
                • <strong>Meals on Wheels:</strong> Home-delivered meals for homebound seniors
              </li>
              <li>• <strong>Senior centers:</strong> Free meals in community settings</li>
              <li>• No income requirements — donations accepted but not required</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-3">Community Meals</h3>
            <p class="text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
              Many churches, nonprofits, and community organizations serve free hot meals. Call 211
              or check with local organizations for schedules in your area.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <hr class="my-8 border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-700" />

        <!-- Tips Section -->
        <div class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-4">
            Tips for Getting Food Help
          </h2>
          <div class="bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-6">
            <ul class="space-y-3 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
              <li>
                <strong>Apply for CalFresh even if you're not sure you qualify.</strong> The application
                is free and the worst that can happen is they say no.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>You can use multiple programs.</strong> CalFresh, WIC, and food banks can all
                be used together.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Benefits don't affect immigration status.</strong> CalFresh and WIC are not considered
                for public charge determinations.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Apply quickly if you have an emergency.</strong> CalFresh offers expedited processing
                (within 3 days) if you have very low income or resources.
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <hr class="my-8 border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-700" />

        <!-- Bay Area County Offices -->
        <div class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-4">
            Bay Area County Offices
          </h2>
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
            <div class="bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-4">
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-2">San Francisco</h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
                Human Services Agency<br />1235 Mission St<br />
                <a
                  href="tel:415-557-5000"
                  class="text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-300 hover:underline">415-557-5000</a
                >
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-4">
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-2">Alameda County</h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
                Social Services Agency<br />Multiple locations<br />
                <a
                  href="tel:510-268-2000"
                  class="text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-300 hover:underline">510-268-2000</a
                >
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-4">
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-2">
                Santa Clara County
              </h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
                Social Services Agency<br />Multiple locations<br />
                <a
                  href="tel:408-758-3800"
                  class="text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-300 hover:underline">408-758-3800</a
                >
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-4">
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-2">
                Contra Costa County
              </h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
                Employment & Human Services<br />Multiple locations<br />
                <a
                  href="tel:877-505-4630"
                  class="text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-300 hover:underline">877-505-4630</a
                >
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <hr class="my-8 border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-700" />

        <!-- Final Disclaimer -->
        <div
          class="bg-amber-50 dark:bg-amber-900/20 border-l-4 border-amber-500 p-4 rounded-r-lg mb-8"
        >
          <p class="text-sm text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300">
            <strong>Important Notice:</strong> The information on this page is for general guidance only.
            Program requirements, income limits, and benefits change periodically. This is not a guarantee
            of eligibility or benefits. The only way to determine if you qualify is to apply directly
            to the relevant program. We encourage you to apply even if you're unsure — there's no penalty
            for applying and being found ineligible.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Back Link -->
        <div class="text-center">
          <a href="/eligibility" class="btn-secondary">
            <svg
              class="w-4 h-4 mr-2"
              fill="none"
              stroke="currentColor"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              aria-hidden="true"
            >
              <path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                stroke-width="2"
                d="M10 19l-7-7m0 0l7-7m-7 7h18"></path>
            </svg>
            Back to Eligibility Guides
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
